<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-05T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-05T08:00:00-05:00" n="279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d279">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/760</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Christiania</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-05T14:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>410. I have received from all members of Russian Legation and from
                                Russian Consul here note stating that they do not recognize the <pb facs="0361" n="287" xml:id="pg_287"/> Bolshevik usurpers at
                                Petrograd as having any legal authority. These notes have been
                                acknowledged without comment. Minister for Foreign Affairs informs
                                me that Norwegian Government has merely acknowledged without comment
                                    <persName corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName>’s notification
                                and that this Government will not recognize the government of
                                Bolsheviks until the great powers do so.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Schmedeman</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>